Ventral idiosoma (
Fig. 12
). Sternal, genital, endopodal and ventral shields fused to form a strongly ornamented composite shield ( 292–293 × 178–179 wide) with ten pairs of setae include the metasternal setae st 4 , which are absent in the female, and two pairs of pores, posterior margin straight. Anal shield free, subtriangular and large ( 64–66 × 128 wide), surface with polygonal ornamentation, para-anal setae equal in length to unpaired post-anal seta, cribrum small, anal pores on edge of shield.
